<br>
You're experiencing 3 problems here.<br>
<br>
1.  Just plain idiots.  Sure the epic can be helpful in some situations, no one's a moron for having it - these are probably the same people that would say the stats on the epic suck because they have their +100243 everything piece from their 24/7 guild raids on the Plane of Lifeless Uberosity, and if you don't WTF loser.  Ignore the silly @#%$.<br>
<br>
2.  Backlash STILL exists from a few arrogant mages in the pre-pop days, as well as some other @#%$, who rated mages as &quot;worthless&quot; without the epic.  This is akin to people saying &quot;Cleric without epic?  No thanks.&quot;  Created some serious resentment toward epic mage wielders.  I'm not saying this makes it right for them to yell at you, but as some insight as to why some still have issues.  These individuals often chill out once they realize you are not claiming some vast superiority over them.<br>
<br>
3.  People that make the assumption that by saying you have the epic pet in a LFG comment, you're stating &quot;I'm better than all the non-epic mages so hah pick me.&quot;  Often people that are already having a bad day here, thus are sort of reading the worst into any message.  These folks often calm down once it becomes clear that you are not being arrogant, just stating an additonal qualification that might be helpful.  <br>
<br>
Summation:  Categories 2 and 3 are sometimes not actually complete assholes - and may be worth working with once they calm down and realize you aren't running around knocking non-epic mages.  Category 1 - screw em - they're jackasses anyway.<br>
<br>
Postscript:  No I do not have the epic, nor do I plan to get it - don't care to spend that level of time or money.  But unless I run into a genuinely arrogant mage, who claims utter superiority over me by virtue of the gumball machine - I will not sit there and give them hell for having it.  More power to them I say - it's all good.  <br>
<br>
Luck in your travels, neighbor.<br>
<br>
